# Argos installer — environment template.
#
# `install.sh` copies this file to `.env` on first install, generates the
# secret values (APP_KEY, ADMIN_PASSWORD, ARGOS_DB_*_PASSWORD) and leaves the
# rest at their defaults. On update it merges any NEW keys from this file into
# your `.env` without touching existing values.
#
# Edit `.env` (not this file), then `docker compose up -d`. Only the keys below
# are meant to be set by hand — everything else has a sane default in the app
# config / compose file. The full menu of advanced overrides (worker limits,
# queue sizes, live-demo tuning, …) is documented in docs/CONFIGURATION.md.
#
# OAuth apps (GitHub/GitLab/Bitbucket/Linear) and the Claude token are NOT set
# here anymore — they are managed in the UI (Configuration → OAuth Apps and the
# onboarding wizard) and stored in the database.

# ── Required ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Public URL the instance is reached on. Single source of truth: OAuth
# callbacks, links, the session cookie domain and the live-demo subdomains all
# derive from it. Defaults to http://localhost:${ARGOS_PORT} if left blank.
APP_URL=

# Host port the nginx container listens on. Map your reverse proxy here.
ARGOS_PORT=8080

# Released templates pin a version (e.g. argos-app:0.2.0); develop tracks
# :latest. Worker images are built on demand by the manager — no separate tag.
ARGOS_APP_IMAGE=ghcr.io/nodus-it/argos-app:latest

# ── Secrets (generated by the installer — keep stable across restarts) ───────
# Back this file up: losing APP_KEY makes all encrypted data unreadable, losing
# the DB passwords locks you out of the database.
APP_KEY=
ADMIN_PASSWORD=
ARGOS_DB_PASSWORD=
ARGOS_DB_ROOT_PASSWORD=

# ── Live demos (optional) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Ephemeral per-task demo deployments, routed by Traefik under their own
# subdomain. Off by default. Requires wildcard DNS *.<host> resolving to this
# host. Base domain + scheme derive from APP_URL — set the two overrides below
# only if demos live on a different domain than the app. TTL, access protection
# (none|session|basic) and resource caps have defaults; see docs/CONFIGURATION.md.
# ARGOS_PREVIEW_ENABLED=true
# ARGOS_PREVIEW_BASE_DOMAIN=
# ARGOS_PREVIEW_SCHEME=
